<p>-- Timothy Ferriss - The 4 Hour Workweek</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1pl2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1pl2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pl2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1pl2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pl2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1pl2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1pl2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1pl2" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1pl2')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1pl2 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1pl2" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1pl2" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1pl2" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1psr" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1psr" class="parent"><a name="1psr" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1psr" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1psr" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1psr" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 March 2010 02:50:21PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1psr'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1psr')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1psr" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1psr" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 March 2010 02:50:21PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1psr'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1psr'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1psr')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1psr" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>For me, the answer is invariably "no". I never do <em>anything</em> important. Therefore this procedure doesn't help me very much.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1psr"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1psr" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1psr')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1psr" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1psr')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1psr" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1psr?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1psr" href="#1pl2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1psr" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1psr')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1psr class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1psr" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1pld" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1pld" class="parent"><a name="1pld" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1pld" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1pld" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1pld" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 March 2010 06:23:04AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pld'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1pld')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1pld" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1pld" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 March 2010 06:23:04AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1pld'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pld'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1pld')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1pld" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Does pure recreational enjoyment count?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1pld"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1pld" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pld')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1pld" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pld')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1pld" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1pld?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1pld" href="#1pl2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1pld" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1pld')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1pld class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1pld" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1pld" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1pld" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1pqh" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1pqh" class="parent"><a name="1pqh" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1pqh" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1pqh" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1pqh" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/roland/">roland</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 March 2010 12:32:52AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pqh'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1pqh')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1pqh" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1pqh" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/roland/">roland</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 March 2010 12:32:52AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1pqh'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pqh'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1pqh')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1pqh" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>After I answered your comment I still had to think about it and I had to add the following. Often it's hard to separate serious reading from enjoyment: for example you could be reading reddit or <a href="http://news.ycombinator.com" rel="nofollow">hackernews</a> either knowing that you are just doing it for entertainment or rationalizing it by thinking you are doing serious reading not realizing that the real reason is the dopamine rush you get. How much time are you willing to spend on random internet reading and other time wasters? You have to judge it yourself. But if you are investing a large amount of your time into that maybe it's good to start reevaluating your information diet.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1pqh"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1pqh" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pqh')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1pqh" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pqh')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1pqh" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1pqh?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1pqh" href="#1pld" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1pqh" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1pqh')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1pqh class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1pqh" cl