g.com/user/AngryParsley/">AngryParsley</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 02:23:05PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1pce'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pce'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1pce')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1pce" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Ditto. On the Mohs scale of sci-fi hardness, Blindsight is aggregated diamond nanorod.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1pce"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1pce" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pce')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1pce" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pce')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1pce" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1pce?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1pce" href="#1pai" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1pce" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1pce')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1pce class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1pce" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1pce" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1pce" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1pdk" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1pdk" class="parent"><a name="1pdk" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1pdk" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1pdk" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1pdk" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Clippy/">Clippy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 04:54:49PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pdk'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1pdk')">[+] (7 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1pdk" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1pdk" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Clippy/">Clippy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 04:54:49PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1pdk'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pdk'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1pdk')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1pdk" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>The Mohs scale is used to rank hardness of solids.  It does not measure faithfulness of books to the science fiction ideal.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1pdk"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1pdk" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pdk')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1pdk" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pdk')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1pdk" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1pdk?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1pdk" href="#1pce" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1pdk" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1pdk')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1pdk class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1pdk" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1pdk" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1pdk" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1pds" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1pds" class="parent"><a name="1pds" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1pds" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1pds" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1pds" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/thomblake/">thomblake</a></span></strong></spa