Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1pds class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1pds" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1pe2" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1pe2" class="parent"><a name="1pe2" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1pe2" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1pe2" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1pe2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/AngryParsley/">AngryParsley</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 05:36:41PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pe2'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1pe2')">[+] (5 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1pe2" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1pe2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/AngryParsley/">AngryParsley</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 05:36:41PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1pe2'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pe2'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1pe2')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1pe2" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>According to V. S. Ramachandran, schizophrenics lack the ability to understand or create metaphors.</p>

<p>I didn't want to link to the massive time vacuum that is TV tropes, but I figured people would understand the metaphor even if they hadn't run in to it before.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1pe2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1pe2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pe2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1pe2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pe2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1pe2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1pe2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1pe2" href="#1pdk" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1pe2" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1pe2')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1pe2 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1pe2" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1pe2" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1pe2" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1phh" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1phh" class="parent"><a name="1phh" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1phh" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1phh" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1phh" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/FAWS/">FAWS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 11:42:11PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1phh'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1phh')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1phh" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1phh" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/FAWS/">FAWS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 11:42:11PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1phh'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1phh'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1phh')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1phh" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>People yes. Paperclip maximizers/office assistants no.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1phh"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1phh" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1phh')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1phh" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1phh')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1phh" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1phh?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1phh" href="#1pe2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1phh" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1phh')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1phh class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1phh" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1pen" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1pen" class="parent"><a name="1pen" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1pen" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1pen" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1pen" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Clippy/">Clippy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 06:51:53PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pen'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1pen')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1pen" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1pen" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Clippy/">Clippy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 06:51:53PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1pen'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pen'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1pen')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1pen" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I understand metaphors.  I just don't understand why there would be a need for scale for science fiction writing.  It's much more important to be able to look up material properties.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1pen"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1pen" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pen')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1pen" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pen')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1pen" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1pen?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1pen" href="#1pe2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1pen" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1pen')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1pen class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1pen" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1pen" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1pen" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1phq" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1phq" class="parent"><a name="1phq" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1phq" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1phq" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1phq" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Jack/">Jack</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 March 2010 12:13:12AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1phq'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1phq')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1phq" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1phq" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Jack/">Jack</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 March 2010 12:13:12AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1phq'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1phq'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1phq')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1phq" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>What about a scale that tells us how much a work of fiction deals with paperclip manufacturing and resource harvesting? Surely you need some way of communicating the traditions and norms of paperclip creating to your youth.</p>

<p>Edit: and come to think of it wouldn't you be interested in in fictional explorations of possible future ways of manufacturing paperclips? And wouldn't you want to know which of those explorations was the least fantasy and most based on reasonable extrapolations from current knowledge?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1phq"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1phq" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1phq')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1phq" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1phq')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1phq" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1phq?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1phq" href="#1pen" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1phq" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1phq')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1phq class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1phq" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1phq" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1phq" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1pq6" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1pq6" class="parent"><a name="1pq6" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1pq6" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1pq6" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1pq6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Clippy/">Clippy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 March 2010 12:08:16AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pq6'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1pq6')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1pq6" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1pq6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Clippy/">Clippy</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 March 2010 12:08:16AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1pq6'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pq6'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1pq6')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1pq6" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>What about a scale that tells us how much a work of fiction deals with paperclip manufacturing and resource harvesting?... wouldn't you be interested in in fictional explorations of possible future ways of manufacturing paperclips? And wouldn't you want to know which of those explorations was the least fantasy and most based on reasonable extrapolations from current knowledge?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>In theory, yes.  In practice, humans have very little to offer in terms of the ultra-efficient methods of paperclip production I normally use.  I don't expect any book to be rated higher than 1, if you compare to what I already have.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Surely you need some way of communicating the traditions and norms of paperclip creating to your youth.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>What are you talking about?  I don't have to do biological self-replication (or sexual semi-replication at the genetic level) like humans do.  I just make a perfect copy of myself.  It already has all my knowledge and values.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1pq6"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1pq6" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pq6')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1pq6" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pq6')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1pq6" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1pq6?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1pq6" href="#1phq" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1pq6" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1pq6')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1pq6 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1pq6" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1phg" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1phg" class="parent"><a name="1phg" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1phg" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1phg" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1phg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/h-H/">h-H</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 11:37:18PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1phg'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1phg')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1phg" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1phg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/h-H/">h-H</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 11:37:18PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1phg'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1phg'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1phg')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1phg" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>actually it's not that easy to see the tvtropes connection, I mean I spend quite a while on tvtropes when I go there-who doesn't?- but in never crossed my mind that that was what you meant.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1phg"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1phg" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1phg')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1phg" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1phg')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1phg" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1phg?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1phg" href="#1pe2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1phg" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1phg')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1phg class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1phg" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1psm" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1psm" class="parent">