<p>Even this isn't true!</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p0j"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p0j" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p0j')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p0j" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p0j')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p0j" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p0j?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p0j" href="#1p0d" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p0j" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p0j')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p0j class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p0j" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p0g" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p0g" class="parent"><a name="1p0g" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p0g" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p0g" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p0g" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Morendil/">Morendil</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 04:26:02PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p0g'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p0g')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p0g" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p0g" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Morendil/">Morendil</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 04:26:02PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p0g'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p0g'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p0g')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p0g" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>the world does appear to be flat, so I think it is incumbent on others to prove decisively that it isn't.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>I haven't yet tracked down a good quote on this type of "asymmetric intellectual warfare", where one advances some outlandish claim that lays waste to large portions of a consistent belief network, and then insists it's the victim's obligation to repair the damage. I'm pretty sure the idea has been around for a while, perhaps not in terms of that military metaphor. Is that topic covered somewhere in the Sequences?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p0g"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p0g" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p0g')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p0g" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p0g')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p0g" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p0g?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p0g" href="#1p0d" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p0g" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p0g')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p0g class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p0g" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1p0g" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1p0g" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1pwp" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1pwp" class="parent"><a name="1pwp" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1pwp" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1pwp" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1pwp" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/HughRistik/">HughRistik</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 March 2010 12:44:19AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pwp'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1pwp')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1pwp" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1pwp" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/HughRistik/">HughRistik</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 March 2010 12:44:19AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1pwp'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1pwp'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1pwp')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1pwp" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It's clearly an abuse of the concept of the Burden of Proof. Along with some motivated skepticism.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1pwp"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1pwp" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pwp')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1pwp" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1pwp')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1pwp" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1pwp?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1pwp" href="#1p0g" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1pwp" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1pwp')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1pwp class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1pwp" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p0t" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p0t" class="parent"><a name="1p0t" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p0t" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p0t" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p0t" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ata/">ata</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 05:24:13PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p0t'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p0t')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p0t" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p0t" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ata/">ata</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 05:24:13PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p0t'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p0t'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p0t')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p0t" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It's not presented in terms of information warfare, and it doesn't explicitly cover "insist[ing] it's the victim's obligation to repair the damage", but the original article on <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/uy/dark_side_epistemology/">Dark Side Epistemology</a> (now known as "anti-epistemology", I hear) sounds similar to what you're getting at. Specifically, the point that to deny one scientific fact, you need to deny a massive network of principles and implications, to the point that your entire epistemology ends up either contradictory or useless.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p0t"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p0t" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p0t')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p0t" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p0t')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p0t" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p0t?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p0t" href="#1p0g" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p0t" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p0t')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p0t class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p0t" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p0w" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p0w" class="parent"><a name="1p0w" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p0w" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p0w" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p0w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Karl_Smith/">Karl_Smith</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 05:57:44PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p0w'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p0w')">[+] (14 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p0w" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p0w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Karl_Smith/">Karl_Smith</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 05:57:44PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p0w'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p0w'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p0w')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p0w" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I just read their website.</p>

<p>Its embarrassing but I have to say that honestly the centripetal force argument never occurred to me before. Rough calculations seem to indicate that a large man 100Kg should be almost half a pound heavier in the day time as he is at night. Kinda cool.</p>

<p>Now I am dying to get something big and stable enough to see if my home scale can pick it up.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p0w"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p0w" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p0w')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p0w" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p0w')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p0w" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p0w?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p0w" href="#1p0d" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p0w" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p0w')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p0w class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p0w" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1p0w" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1p0w" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p14" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p14" class="parent"><a name="1p14" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p14" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p14" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p14" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RolfAndreassen/">RolfAndreassen</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 06:26:23PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p14'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p14')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p14" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p14" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RolfAndreassen/">RolfAndreassen</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 06:26:23PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p14'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p14'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p14')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p14" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Don't forget to adjust your calculations for not being on the equator, and to take into account that 'nighttime' is not equivalent to 'the Sun pulls you directly towards the center of the Earth'. Both tend to make the effect smaller.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p14"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p14" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p14')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p14" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p14')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p14" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p14?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p14" href="#1p0w" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p14" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p14')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p14 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p14" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p1p" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p1p" class="parent"><a name="1p1p" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p1p" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p1p" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p1p" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Eliezer_Yudkowsky/">Eliezer_Yudkowsky</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 07:35:31PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p1p'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p1p')">[+] (12 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p1p" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p1p" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Eliezer_Yudkowsky/">Eliezer_Yudkowsky</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 07:35:31PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p1p'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p1p'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p1p')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p1p" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Quick look didn't find it, but I don't see why this follows (and at a wild guess, I'm guessing it doesn't).  Can you link?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p1p"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p1p" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p1p')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p1p" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p1p')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p1p" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p1p?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p1p" href="#1p0w" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p1p" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p1p')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p1p class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p1p" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1p1p" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1p1p" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p3a" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p3a" class="parent"><a name="1p3a" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p3a" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p3a" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p3a" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RolfAndreassen/">RolfAndreassen</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 09:47:17PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p3a'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p3a')">[+] (10 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p3a" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p3a" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RolfAndreassen/">RolfAndreassen</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 09:47:17PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p3a'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p3a'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p3a')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p3a" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>As you stand on the equator, with the Sun directly overhead, its gravity is pulling you away from the Earth's center. On the other side of the Earth, the Sun's gravity pulls you in towards its center. Consequently you weigh slightly less at noon than at midnight. However, since the force of the Sun's gravity on a 100-kg mass 1 AU distant is about 0.006 Newton, an average bathroom scale is not going to notice.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p3a"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p3a" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p3a')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p3a" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p3a')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p3a" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p3a?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p3a" href="#1p1p" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p3a" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p3a')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p3a class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p3a" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1p3a" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1p3a" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p4y" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p4y" class="parent"><a name="1p4y" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p4y" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p4y" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p4y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Eliezer_Yudkowsky/">Eliezer_Yudkowsky</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 11:20:47PM</span><span class="votes " >9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p4y'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p4y')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p4y" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p4y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Eliezer_Yudkowsky/">Eliezer_Yudkowsky</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 11:20:47PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p4y'>9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p4y'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p4y')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p4y" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>And the Earth is slowly curving in its orbit, generating an apparent centrifugal force that decreases your weight at midnight, and increases your weight at noon.  Except for a very tiny tidal correction, these two forces <em>exactly cancel</em> which is <em>why the Earth stays in orbit in the first place</em>.  This argument would only be valid if the Earth were suspended motionless on two giant poles running through the axis or something.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p4y"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p4y" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p4y')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p4y" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p4y')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p4y" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p4y?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p4y" href="#1p3a" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p4y" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p4y')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p4y class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p4y" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1p4y" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1p4y" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p5f" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p5f" class="parent"><a name="1p5f" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p5f" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p5f" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p5f" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RolfAndreassen/">RolfAndreassen</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 11:57:17PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p5f'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p5f')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p5f" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p5f" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RolfAndreassen/">RolfAndreassen</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 11:57:17PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p5f'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p5f'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p5f')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p5f" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>The Earth is a (fairly) rigid body held together by its internal structure, and is not required to be moving at orbital velocity at every point on its surface. That is, the effect you mention exists, but it is not clear that it exactly cancels the gravitational effect. (Or equivalently, it's not obvious that the tidal effect is small.) Don't forget that the Earth's rotation is reducing your effective orbital velocity on the day-side, and increasing it on the night-side.</p>

<p>Now, if you have some numbers showing that the cancellation is close to exact for the specific case of the Earth, that's fine. An argument showing that it's always going to be close to exact for planet-sized bodies in orbit around stars would also be convincing.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p5f"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p5f" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p5f')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p5f" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p5f')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p5f" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p5f?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p5f" href="#1p4y" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p5f" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p5f')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p5f class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p5f" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1p5f" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1p5f" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p5j" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p5j" class="parent"><a name="1p5j" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p5j" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p5j" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p5j" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 12:07:11AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p5j'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p5j')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p5j" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p5j" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 March 2010 12:07:11AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p5j'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p5j'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p5j')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p5j" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>According to Wikipedia, solar tides are about 0.52*10^-7 g, as opposed to lunar tides of about 1.1*10^-7 g. One part in twenty million and one part in ten million, respectively.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p5j"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p5j" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p5j')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p5j" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p5j')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p5j" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p5j?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p5j" href="#1p5f" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p5j" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p5j')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p5j class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p5j" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p61" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1p61" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1p61" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p61" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1p61" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1p61" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_1p61" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_1ud', ['1p61'], 5)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(2 replies)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p61"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p61" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p3o" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p3o" class="parent"><a name="1p3o" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p3o" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p3o" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p3o" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/jimrandomh/">jimrandomh</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 09:57:45PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p3o'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p3o')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p3o" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p3o" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/jimrandomh/">jimrandomh</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 09:57:45PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p3o'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p3o'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p3o')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p3o" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>No, because it pulls you, your scale and the Earth all (very close to) equally.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1p3o"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1p3o" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p3o')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1p3o" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1p3o')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1p3o" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1ud/rationality_quotes_march_2010/1p3o?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1p3o" href="#1p3a" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1p3o" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1p3o')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1p3o class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1p3o" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1p3o" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1p3o" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1p3s" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1p3s" class="parent"><a name="1p3s" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1p3s" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1p3s" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1p3s" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 10:02:39PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p3s'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1p3s')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1p3s" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1p3s" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 March 2010 10:02:39PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1p3s'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1p3s'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1p3s')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1p3s" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I feel like an idiot for not seeing this earlier: you're right; this is the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tidal_force" rel="nofollow">tidal force</a> problem.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>More precisely, the lunar tidal acceleration (along the Moon-Earth axis, at the Earth's surface) is about 1.1 × 10−7 g, while the solar tidal acceleration (along the Sun-Earth axis, at the Earth's surface) is about 0.52 × 10−7 g, where g is the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_gravity" rel="nofollow">gravitational acceleration</a> at the Earth's surface.</p>
</blockquote>

